data.enText: a man's (usually a married man's) mistress is a woman that he is having a regular sexual relationship with and who is not his wife
a female teacher in a school, especially a private school

data.chText: （尤指旧时雇用仆人的）女主人，主妇
data.enText: (in the past) the female head of a house, especially one who employed servants
the female owner of a dog or other animal

data.chText: 有权势的女子；女能人；女强人；女主宰
data.enText: a woman who is in a position of authority or control, or who is highly skilled in sth

data.chText: 她希望自己的事自己作主。
data.enText: She wants to be mistress of her own affairs (= to organize her own life) .

tr: a woman master who directs the work of others
a woman who has an ongoing extramarital sexual relationship with a man
a woman schoolteacher (especially one regarded as strict)

value.def: A married man's mistress is a woman who is not his wife and with whom he is having a sexual relationship.

example.ex: She was his mistress for three years...
He has a wife and a mistress.
example.tran: 他有妻子，还有一个情妇。

example.ex: My history mistress was extremely helpful.
example.tran: 教我历史的那位女老师特别乐于助人。

value.def: A servant's mistress is the woman that he or she works for.

example.ex: It must be really bad, for her to ignore a summons from her mistress!
example.tran: 她居然不听女主人的使唤，实在是太不像话了！

value.def: A dog's mistress is the woman or girl who owns it.

example.ex: The huge wolfhound danced in circles around his mistress.
example.tran: 这条大狼犬围着女主人蹦蹦跳跳地绕圈子。

value.def: If a woman is mistress of a situation, she has complete control over it.

example.ex: She had always been mistress of her own destiny.
example.tran: 她总是能够掌握自己的命运。

gramarinfo.label: also N in pl, usu N <l>of</l> n

value.tran: 绝对控制…的女人；主宰…的女人

value.def: If you say that a woman is a mistress of a particular activity, you mean that she is very skilled at it.

example.ex: She is a mistress of disguise.
...another winner from the mistress of historical romance.
example.tran: 来自这位历史爱情小说知名女作家又一部必定大受欢迎的作品

value.tran: (精通某项活动的)女能手，女行家
